        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 3:30PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 329 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Comer, or near
Danielsville, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, up to penny sized hail and frequent
cloud to ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Comer, Carlton, Watson Mill Bridge State Park, and Paoli.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
